{
    "_template": "Phoenix Toolbox — Hooks Configuration Template",
    "_description": [
          "Hooks are lifecycle event handlers that fire at specific points during",
          "a Claude Code session. They enable capabilities to inject behavior",
          "automatically without requiring explicit user commands.",
          "",
          "Available hook events:",
          "  - SessionStart: Fires when a new Claude Code session begins",
          "  - SessionEnd: Fires when a session is ending",
          "  - PreToolUse: Fires before a tool is executed (can modify/block)",
          "  - PostToolUse: Fires after a tool completes (can react to results)",
          "  - Notification: Fires on system notifications",
          "",
          "Reference: capabilities/echo-persistence/hooks/ (3 production hooks)",
          "Reference: capabilities/phoenix-comms/hooks/ (3 production hooks)",
          "Guide: docs/PLUGIN_DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md (Section 6: Hooks)"
    ],

    "hooks": [
          {
                  "event": "SessionStart",
                  "description": "{{HOOK_DESCRIPTION}} — Runs when session begins",
                  "enabled": true,
                  "priority": 10,
                  "action": {
                            "type": "{{ACTION_TYPE}}",
                            "target": "{{ACTION_TARGET}}",
                            "parameters": {}
                  },
                  "_notes": [
                            "SessionStart hooks are ideal for:",
                            "  - Loading context files (buffers, configs, state)",
                            "  - Checking for pending tasks or missions",
                            "  - Verifying environment prerequisites",
                            "  - Setting session-level variables",
                            "",
                            "Priority: Lower numbers run first. Default is 10.",
                            "Use 1-5 for critical initialization, 10 for standard, 20+ for optional.",
                            "",
                            "Action types:",
                            "  - 'read_file': Read a file into context",
                            "  - 'execute_command': Run a slash command",
                            "  - 'check_condition': Evaluate a condition before proceeding",
                            "  - 'notify': Display a notification to the user"
                  ]
          },
          {
                  "event": "PreToolUse",
                  "description": "{{HOOK_DESCRIPTION}} — Runs before tool execution",
                  "enabled": true,
                  "priority": 10,
                  "tool_filter": "{{TOOL_NAME_OR_PATTERN}}",
                  "action": {
                            "type": "{{ACTION_TYPE}}",
                            "target": "{{ACTION_TARGET}}",
                            "parameters": {}
                  },
                  "_notes": [
                            "PreToolUse hooks intercept tool calls before execution.",
                            "Use cases:",
                            "  - Validate parameters before dangerous operations",
                            "  - Block forbidden actions (e.g., rm, delete)",
                            "  - Log tool usage for audit trails",
                            "  - Modify tool parameters (add safety flags, etc.)",
                            "",
                            "tool_filter: Which tool(s) trigger this hook.",
                            "  - Exact match: 'Bash' (only Bash tool)",
                            "  - Pattern: 'Bash|Write' (Bash or Write tools)",
                            "  - Wildcard: '*' (all tools)",
                            "",
                            "IMPORTANT: PreToolUse hooks that block operations should",
                            "provide clear error messages explaining WHY and what to do instead."
                  ]
          },
          {
                  "event": "PostToolUse",
                  "description": "{{HOOK_DESCRIPTION}} — Runs after tool execution",
            "enabled": true,
            "priority": 10,
            "tool_filter": "{{TOOL_NAME_OR_PATTERN}}",
            "action": {
          "type": "{{ACTION_TYPE}}",
                      "target": "{{ACTION_TARGET}}",
                      "parameters": {}
            },
            "_notes": [
          "PostToolUse hooks react to completed tool executions.",
                      "Use cases:",
                      "  - Log results for audit/history",
                      "  - Trigger follow-up actions based on results",
                      "  - Update state files after modifications",
                      "  - Send notifications on specific outcomes"
            ]
      },
          {
                  "event": "SessionEnd",
                  "description": "{{HOOK_DESCRIPTION}} — Runs when session is ending",
            "enabled": true,
            "priority": 10,
            "action": {
          "type": "{{ACTION_TYPE}}",
                      "target": "{{ACTION_TARGET}}",
                      "parameters": {}
            },
            "_notes": [
          "SessionEnd hooks handle cleanup and persistence.",
                      "Use cases:",
                      "  - Save session state to buffer files",
                      "  - Commit uncommitted work",
                      "  - Post checkpoint comments",
                      "  - Archive session logs",
                      "",
                      "CRITICAL: SessionEnd hooks must be fast and reliable.",
                      "If Chrome is crashing, complex hooks may not complete."
            ]
      }
],

    "_configuration": {
          "capability": "{{CAPABILITY_NAME}}",
          "version": "1.0.0",
          "author": "{{AUTHOR}}",
          "created": "{{DATE}}",
          "last_updated": "{{DATE}}"
    }
}
